article.description: Kara Braxton scored 30 points and grabbed 11 rebounds as No. 17 Georgia defeated UCLA 91-83 on Friday.
article.headline: Lady Bulldogs stop Bruins, avoid three-game skid
article.linkText: Braxton powers No. 17 Georgia past UCLA
article.story:
ATHENS, Ga. (Ticker) -- Kara Braxton scored 30 points and grabbed 11 rebounds as No. 17 Georgia defeated UCLA 91-83 on Friday.

The Lady Bulldogs avoided a three-game losing streak.  Georgia (3-2) lost at Arizona and at Arizona State after winning a pair of road games to start the season.

Braxton was one of three players to post double-doubles for Georgia. Christi Thomas collected 23 points and 11 rebounds, while Mary Beth Lycett had 17 and 13, adding seven assists.

UCLA (4-2) trailed by 20 points at halftime but clawed back into
the game with eight 3-pointers in the second half, including
four by Lisa Willis, who scored 12 points in 18 minutes off the
bench before fouling out.

Julia Pitts led the Bruins with 20 points on 8-of-10 shooting. Michelle Greco added 12 points and eight rebounds for UCLA, which was outrebounded 51-36.

UCLA had a four-game winning streak stopped.
